Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.92,0:00:06.13,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,Alchemy is a science where one understands the structure of matter, breaks it down, then rebuilds it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.13,0:00:11.74,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,However, it is not an all-powerful technique,\Nas one cannot create something out of nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.45,0:00:17.53,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,If one wishes to gain something,\None must present something of equal value.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.53,0:00:22.29,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,This is the concept of equivalent exchange, the fundamental basis of alchemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.87,0:00:26.89,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,However, there is a taboo in alchemy. Human transmutation.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.89,0:00:29.21,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,One must not commit this act.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.72,0:02:04.14,Default-alt,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}To you, children of God, who live on this earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.14,0:02:07.80,Default-alt,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}pray and believe, and you shall be saved.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.38,0:02:11.81,Default-alt,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}The Sun God Leto shines light upon you to show you the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.47,0:02:11.81,Default,Man,0000,0000,0000,,Are you guys street performers or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.20,0:02:16.42,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Where in the world did you get that idea?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.42,0:02:17.69,Default,Man,0000,0000,0000,,Am I wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.69,0:02:19.03,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for the meal.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.10,0:02:23.97,Default,Man,0000,0000,0000,,Hey now, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.97,0:02:26.22,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry about that, we'll fix it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.22,0:02:27.79,Default,Man,0000,0000,0000,,"Fix", you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.79,0:02:29.29,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Well, just watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.29,0:02:33.63,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Well then, here I go!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.84,0:02:39.60,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,How's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.60,0:02:41.51,Default,Man,0000,0000,0000,,Now that's quite a surprise.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.51,0:02:44.03,Default,Man,0000,0000,0000,,You're able to perform miracles, as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.03,0:02:45.39,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,What the heck are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.39,0:02:47.42,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,We're alchemists.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.42,0:02:50.15,Default,Man,0000,0000,0000,,That's the first time I've seen anything like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.15,0:02:52.48,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,You've never heard of us, the Elric Brothers, before?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.48,0:02:54.18,Default,Man,0000,0000,0000,,"Elric"?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.18,0:02:55.96,Default,Man2,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, I have.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.96,0:02:58.74,Default,Man3,0000,0000,0000,,The Fullmetal Alchemist, Edward Elric!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.74,0:03:02.43,Default,Man3,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, so you're that rumored genius alchemist.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.43,0:03:06.26,Default,Man3,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, I get it! Your other name is "Fullmetal" because of this suit!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.26,0:03:09.29,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,No... You have the wrong person...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.76,0:03:13.92,Default,Man,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? That little guy over there?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.92,0:03:16.63,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you calling a pea-sized runt?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.01,0:03:21.72,Default-alt,Corn,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Pray and believe...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.42,0:03:22.63,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,So, what the heck is this broadcast?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.63,0:03:25.55,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,I-It's the High Priest Cornello...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.50,0:03:31.50,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,He came here a few years ago and preached to us about the path of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.50,0:03:35.73,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,"God will grant eternity to the living and resurrection to the dead."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.73,0:03:38.07,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,And proof of it all are the miracles that he produces.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.07,0:03:41.92,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,"Resurrection to the dead", eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.35,0:03:43.82,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds fishy to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.04,0:03:58.88,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,That's what they were talking about, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.88,0:04:00.17,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.17,0:04:03.68,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,It's pretty obvious from that transmutation response that it's alchemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.68,0:04:06.55,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,But he's totally ignoring the concept of equivalent exchange.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.55,0:04:11.18,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,It's a rule that you can only produce something from matter of equal value.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.18,0:04:13.72,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,He changed a flower to a mineral, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.16,0:04:15.96,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Brother, could it be...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.96,0:04:17.96,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. It could be...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.10,0:04:20.25,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Bingo.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.15,0:04:33.87,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,God... please listen to my wish...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.70,0:04:35.58,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,Please bring back-
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.58,0:04:37.96,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, so this is Mr. Leto.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.13,0:04:41.13,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,Are you interested in the religion of Leto?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.13,0:04:44.13,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Nah. Unfortunately, I'm an atheist.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.30,0:04:46.91,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,That's not good.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.33,0:04:51.68,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,Believing and honoring God,\Nand living in gratitude and hope...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.24,0:04:54.03,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,How glorious.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.80,0:04:56.10,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,If you believe...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.84,0:04:58.94,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure you'll grow taller!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.94,0:05:00.33,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,What did you say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.33,0:05:02.65,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,She didn't mean it in a bad way!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.55,0:05:05.94,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,"Resurrection to the dead"...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.71,0:05:08.72,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Do you seriously believe something like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.72,0:05:09.33,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.87,0:05:14.86,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Water, 35L.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.86,0:05:16.45,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Carbon, 20kg.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.45,0:05:17.95,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Ammonia, 4L.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.95,0:05:19.88,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Lime, 1.5kg.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.88,0:05:21.54,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Phosphorus, 800g.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.54,0:05:23.25,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Salt, 250g.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.25,0:05:24.55,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Niter, 100g.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.55,0:05:26.29,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,And others.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.29,0:05:27.38,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,...What?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.52,0:05:33.48,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Those are the ingredients that make up an average adult human body.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.80,0:05:40.15,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,{\fscx96}We know this from our advances in science, but there\Nhaven't been any reports of successful human transmutations.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.11,0:05:44.53,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,You really think that praying would solve something that even science couldn't solve?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.53,0:05:48.91,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,"Pray and believe, and your wishes shall be."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.91,0:05:50.03,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,And by the way,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.03,0:05:55.66,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,you can buy these basic ingredients at the market with a kid's pocket money.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.12,0:05:58.58,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Humans are made pretty cheaply, aren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.96,0:06:03.37,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,People are not things. Those words are blasphemy to our creator.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.37,0:06:04.82,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,You'll suffer divine punishment for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.11,0:06:09.05,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Alchemists are scientists, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.39,0:06:12.73,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,We don't believe in creators or the existence of a God.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.39,0:06:17.73,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Looking for the solution to the creation principle of this world and pursuing the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.13,0:06:25.19,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,It's pretty ironic we're the closest things to God\Nin a sense, even though we have no need for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.71,0:06:28.39,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,Are you saying you're on the same level as God?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.93,0:06:29.95,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,How arrogant!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.95,0:06:31.94,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Arrogant, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.27,0:06:34.81,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I remember this from a mythical tale.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.27,0:06:41.96,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,"The hero who gets too close to the sun shall have\Nhis wax wings plucked and be dropped to the earth."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.64,0:06:43.55,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.33,0:06:51.47,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Lady, will Mr. Leto save a scientist like me?\NEven though I was thinking something like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.00,0:06:55.97,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,Of course. He will accept reformers at any time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.12,0:07:00.48,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,High Priest, there are people who wish to have a meeting with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.48,0:07:03.00,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Two of them. A child and a man in a suit of armor.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.00,0:07:05.47,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,They call themselves the "Elric Brothers".
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.47,0:07:08.16,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,I'm busy. Dismiss them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.16,0:07:11.33,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, wait... Did you say... the Elric Brothers?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.33,0:07:14.15,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that's what they said...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.15,0:07:19.22,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,This is going to be trouble.\NIt's the Fullmetal Alchemist, Edward Elric.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.22,0:07:20.99,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,The... man in the armor?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.99,0:07:22.79,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.79,0:07:25.70,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,What is a State Alchemist doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.70,0:07:28.26,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be that our plan has been...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.26,0:07:32.26,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,Those dogs of the military must have a good sense of smell.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.69,0:07:34.80,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,This way, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.37,0:07:39.61,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,The High Priest is a very busy man, and he usually cannot find time for such matters, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.61,0:07:41.27,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,You folks are lucky.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.27,0:07:45.43,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry for the trouble. I'll try to make it quick.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.43,0:07:47.98,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, let's get this over with as quickly as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.40,0:07:53.55,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,Priest, what are you doing?!{I'll find a good term for this later ~koki}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.55,0:07:59.10,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Rose, these people are heathens who are trying to ensnare the High Priest. They are evil.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.10,0:08:00.11,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,No, that's...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.11,0:08:03.75,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,So... let's get this over with quick!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.42,0:08:14.26,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Strike!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.26,0:08:15.63,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,So noisy!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.07,0:08:22.37,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome to the holy order, Fullmetal Alchemist.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.85,0:08:23.85,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,Sir Cornello!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.37,0:08:26.97,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like some of us were rather hasty.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.97,0:08:28.89,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,I apologize for their rudeness.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.89,0:08:32.53,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,It really doesn't feel like an apology when you're looking down at us from a high place like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.53,0:08:34.53,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,Are you here for our dogma?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.53,0:08:40.48,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I have a lot of things I want to learn from you... say,\Na method for tricking your followers with petty alchemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.99,0:08:43.40,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,I have no idea what you're talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.40,0:08:47.00,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,I can't have you putting my miracles and alchemy on the same level.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.97,0:08:51.51,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,How's this? Can this be achieved through alchemy?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.35,0:08:54.43,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,That's precisely what I'm concerned about.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.93,0:08:58.76,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,For some strange reason, you can perform\Ntransmutations while clearly ignoring the rules.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.76,0:09:01.26,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,Which is why it isn't alchemy-
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.26,0:09:03.71,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,So I was thinking...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.71,0:09:12.45,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,If you had the legendary amplifier that allows alchemists to perform the impossible, it would be possible in your case.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.45,0:09:13.29,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.29,0:09:18.45,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Yep. Frankly, the Philosopher's Stone. Isn't that what your ring is made of?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.41,0:09:21.97,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,That was a long search.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.48,0:09:24.29,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,This is just an ordinary ring.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.29,0:09:27.62,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,God has allowed me to perform miracles.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.62,0:09:29.77,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Still gonna play dumb?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.77,0:09:33.38,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Guess I'll have to get my hands on you and ask your body for the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.06,0:09:37.32,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,You seem to be an incorrigible heathen.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.32,0:09:37.88,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,Rose.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.45,0:09:39.43,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.14,0:09:42.39,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,Pick up that pistol.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.80,0:09:44.64,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.89,0:09:50.15,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,Now shoot the Fullmetal Alchemist.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.94,0:09:54.03,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,I... can't do that...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.03,0:09:56.83,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,My words are God's words.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.83,0:09:59.08,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,This is God's will.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.93,0:10:02.03,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,Rose, shoot him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.04,0:10:06.78,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.78,0:10:09.54,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,Who was the one...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.94,0:10:14.63,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,...who rescued you from your despair\Nafter you lost your love in an accident last year?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.53,0:10:17.88,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,It was you, Sir Cornello...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.88,0:10:21.62,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. It was I who rescued you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.62,0:10:23.64,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,And what did I promise you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.89,0:10:26.14,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,That you'd revive him!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.77,0:10:31.19,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Umm... I'm not the one you're supposed to be aiming at...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.44,0:10:36.94,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm{\i0} the Fullmetal Alchemist, got it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.19,0:10:39.07,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, {\i1}you're{\i0} the one?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.87,0:10:45.20,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry... I have to.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.20,0:10:46.95,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,He's a swindler.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.95,0:10:47.78,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,No, he isn't!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.78,0:10:51.33,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,He's going to revive him with his miracles!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.33,0:10:52.83,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Then shoot me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.26,0:10:59.90,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Al!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.64,0:11:07.45,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,Good work. God is rejoicing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.45,0:11:09.89,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,Now, shoot the other.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.49,0:11:12.90,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Man, you make your followers do terrible things.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.90,0:11:13.81,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.19,0:11:16.32,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.32,0:11:18.42,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,As you can see...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.42,0:11:19.82,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,...this is how it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.23,0:11:23.89,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,An empty suit of armor!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.32,0:11:28.27,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,This, itself, is evidence of their evil!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.27,0:11:30.68,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,They must be eliminated!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.52,0:11:39.09,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,Is this your first time seeing a chimera?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.84,0:11:43.76,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,So you made something like this with your Philosopher's Stone, too, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.97,0:11:47.90,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I should probably arm myself...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.56,0:11:57.59,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,Without a transmutation circle?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.59,0:12:01.33,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,I guess your title of "State Alchemist" has to come with {\i1}something{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.33,0:12:02.03,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.99,0:12:10.20,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,How do you like those claws that cut through iron?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.71,0:12:13.25,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Just kidding.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.24,0:12:19.67,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately, my leg is a bit special.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.67,0:12:21.18,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,Bite him to death!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.89,0:12:26.92,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, stupid cat?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.92,0:12:28.76,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Get a good taste of it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.50,0:12:35.81,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,That arm...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.26,0:12:37.81,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,...and a brother without his body...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.25,0:12:40.57,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, I see now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.22,0:12:44.40,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,Fullmetal Alchemist... you...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.40,0:12:46.91,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,You've done it, haven't you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.36,0:12:49.44,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Get down here, third-rate!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.44,0:12:51.95,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I'll show you the difference in our skill!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.16,0:13:00.21,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Get down here, third-rate!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.21,0:13:02.55,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I'll show you the difference in our skill!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.55,0:13:07.57,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,Rose, these guys have committed the greatest taboo alchemists can commit.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.57,0:13:10.40,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,Human transmutation.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.40,0:13:13.68,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,They tried to revive the dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.93,0:13:21.22,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,"The hero who gets too close to the sun shall have\Nhis wax wings plucked and be dropped to the earth."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.31,0:13:23.23,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.74,0:13:27.85,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,This is the body of a sinner who encroached upon God's territory.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.19,0:13:31.25,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Rose, are you really prepared to be like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.73,0:13:34.62,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,Edward Elric.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.62,0:13:38.75,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,And you call yourself a State Alchemist? You make me laugh.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.75,0:13:40.25,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Shut the hell up!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.25,0:13:43.05,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,You can't do anything without\Nthe Philosopher's Stone, third-rate!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.05,0:13:47.26,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,High Priest, please give us the stone before you get hurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.26,0:13:51.81,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,How ridiculous! Fools who stepped into God's territory!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.13,0:13:56.02,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,I'll send you to his side, once and for all!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.45,0:14:07.40,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Nah, God seems to hate me,\Nso he'll probably send me back even if I went.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.95,0:14:14.12,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Al!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.58,0:14:23.21,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?! After them!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.21,0:14:26.46,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,They are heathens who bring evil to the order! Catch them!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.68,0:14:31.03,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Stop right there!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.03,0:14:33.77,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think you can do unarmed, kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.77,0:14:36.66,Default,Guy3,0000,0000,0000,,Just give up before you get hurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.70,0:14:45.69,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Don't let your guard down just because he's a kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.61,0:14:48.36,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Out of the way!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.58,0:14:54.37,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Get it now, Rose?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.79,0:14:58.78,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Cornello shot at us, even though you were with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.78,0:15:00.79,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,But that's because you two...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.17,0:15:06.30,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,Is that story true?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.84,0:15:12.55,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,We just wanted to see Mom's smiling face again.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.93,0:15:15.93,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,But the transmutation failed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.31,0:15:18.97,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,It didn't even look human.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.59,0:15:24.20,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,We learned our mistake the hard way.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.95,0:15:27.90,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,People cannot be revived... even our mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.35,0:15:30.52,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,That's not true... because...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.52,0:15:33.24,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,The fundamental basis of alchemy is the concept of equivalent exchange.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.80,0:15:36.30,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,The price we paid for the human transmutation was huge.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.10,0:15:41.41,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Brother lost his left leg, and I lost my body.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.71,0:15:44.52,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Can you see it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.26,0:15:47.67,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Brother drew it with his blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.42,0:15:52.95,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,It must have been painful for him,\Nafter having his left leg taken away.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.51,0:16:01.02,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,But Brother affixed my soul to this suit and gave up his right arm as compensation.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.44,0:16:06.60,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,I want to fix my brother's body.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.60,0:16:09.44,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Brother wants to get my body back, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.31,0:16:14.41,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,But we may die trying.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.61,0:16:19.45,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,That's the path we've chosen.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.03,0:16:22.35,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,But, Sir Cornello could...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.78,0:16:23.62,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Rose...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.39,0:16:27.61,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you two can't, he could...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.61,0:16:30.65,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,He could do it! He will!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.66,0:16:35.68,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,You brat! You'd better be prepared!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.68,0:16:38.56,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Old man, let's have a heart-to-heart talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.56,0:16:41.28,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I just want to know the secret behind that stone.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.00,0:16:44.84,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Or should I call for the army to mobilize?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.84,0:16:46.69,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,To inspect the stone, that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.31,0:16:51.44,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.44,0:16:54.35,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,What do you plan to do with the Philosopher's Stone?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.73,0:16:57.53,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,You don't need that pitiful order if you have the stone, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.83,0:17:04.91,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,The order will produce followers that will joyfully give up their lives for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.91,0:17:08.00,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,They would be an undefeatable army that does not fear even death.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.00,0:17:09.42,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,Just watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.98,0:17:14.44,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to be stripping this country away in a few years.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.79,0:17:17.65,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,By using the Philosopher's Stone and my stupid followers!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.11,0:17:21.24,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,I guess I could share some of the leftovers with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.92,0:17:25.98,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,What's so funny?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.48,0:17:29.61,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This{\i0} is why I called you third-rate.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.22,0:17:36.95,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,Y...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.95,0:17:38.22,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,You didn't...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.45,0:17:41.96,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,There are no such things as miracles.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.35,0:17:44.53,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,They were all thanks to the power of the Philosopher's Stone.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.48,0:17:47.37,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.37,0:17:48.96,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,When did you flip on that switch?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.96,0:17:49.98,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,When?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.98,0:17:50.96,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,From the very beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.96,0:17:52.96,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,It's all been leaked, now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.96,0:17:54.96,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,What have you done?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.96,0:17:57.16,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,You brat!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.97,0:17:59.55,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Too slow!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.47,0:18:04.22,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Told ya. We're on totally different levels.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.56,0:18:08.19,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,I'm invincible!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.61,0:18:19.24,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,R-Rebound!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.24,0:18:21.91,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not giving up yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.43,0:18:25.43,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,I'm... I'm...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.26,0:18:29.07,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,God's hand!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.70,0:18:54.40,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,My words are God's words. This fist is God's fist!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.40,0:18:57.42,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,"God's fist", you say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.95,0:19:01.20,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,If you like it so much, I'll let you have a taste of it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.59,0:19:20.86,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.30,0:19:22.80,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Now give me the Philosopher's Stone!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.53,0:19:31.54,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,It... broke? What does this mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.01,0:19:36.09,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,How could the Philosopher's Stone break? It's supposed to be a perfect substance!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.09,0:19:37.19,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,I... I don't know!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.19,0:19:38.77,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't hear about this!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.77,0:19:40.02,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,P-P-P-Please don't hurt me!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.02,0:19:42.23,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,Please! I was wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.23,0:19:43.91,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,So it was a fake?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.91,0:19:47.79,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,I can't do anything without the stone! Please, have mercy!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.79,0:19:52.12,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I finally thought we'd be able to get our bodies back, and it's...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.12,0:19:54.54,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,...fake...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.09,0:19:57.42,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,U-Umm, what about me?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.59,0:20:01.09,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Go wherever you want!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.09,0:20:02.43,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.46,0:20:06.76,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,What about the Philosopher's Stone?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.11,0:20:09.18,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,It was a fake.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.78,0:20:10.60,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.14,0:20:15.83,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,And I thought we'd finally be able to get your body back...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.83,0:20:17.43,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,Give me the Philosopher's Stone!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.27,0:20:20.36,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Rose...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.58,0:20:24.73,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't I just say that it was a fake?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.73,0:20:26.70,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,And in any case, it broke on its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.70,0:20:27.52,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,That's a lie!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.82,0:20:29.16,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,You're planning to keep it for yourselves, aren't you!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.07,0:20:32.71,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,To fix your bodies... right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.71,0:20:34.64,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,And you want to meet your mother again, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.04,0:20:35.79,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.26,0:20:39.58,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,The dead cannot be revived...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.10,0:20:40.88,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Never...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.97,0:20:43.88,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Never.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.98,0:20:48.63,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,But he said that he'd be able to bring him back...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.41,0:20:51.14,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,He said that if I prayed, it would come true.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.87,0:20:53.45,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,That a miracle would occur...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.19,0:20:59.27,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,What am I supposed to cling to from now on?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.10,0:21:01.25,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.93,0:21:04.03,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.24,0:21:08.66,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Decide that for yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.57,0:21:13.92,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Get up and take a step. Walk forward.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.73,0:21:17.04,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,You've got two fine legs on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.88,0:21:21.24,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,You don't need to cling to anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.19,0:21:29.53,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.53,0:21:31.38,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Let us see the High Priest!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.38,0:21:33.32,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Were you guys tricking us?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.32,0:21:34.77,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Open this door!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.81,0:21:39.91,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,My plans... ruined by a brat like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.91,0:21:42.44,Default,Lust,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously. What a mess.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.44,0:21:45.53,Default,Lust,0000,0000,0000,,All you had to do was to wreak a bit of havoc.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.53,0:21:46.94,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,You...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.94,0:21:48.31,Default,Glut,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Lust?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.31,0:21:50.45,Default,Glut,0000,0000,0000,,Can I eat this guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.45,0:21:52.56,Default,Lust,0000,0000,0000,,No, Gluttony.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.56,0:21:54.95,Default,Lust,0000,0000,0000,,If you eat something like that, you'll get a stomachache.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.95,0:21:58.00,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,How dare... How dare you all make fun of me!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.59,0:22:05.92,Default,Lust,0000,0000,0000,,You're not needed anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.99,0:22:13.21,Default,Lust,0000,0000,0000,,It was just starting to liven up, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.86,0:22:15.81,Default,Lust,0000,0000,0000,,I guess we have to start over.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.43,0:22:18.31,Default,Lust,0000,0000,0000,,Father will get mad at us.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.96,0:22:22.86,Default,Lust,0000,0000,0000,,Now, I wonder what we should do next...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.34,0:24:06.34,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,Ed and Al visit East City, home of Eastern Headquarters, to report the incident in Lior.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.79,0:24:12.26,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,And they meet Shou Tucker,\Nthe Sewing-Life Alchemist, and his daughter, Nina.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.42,0:24:17.76,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, Fullmetal Alchemist:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.76,0:24:20.77,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 4, An Alchemist's Distress.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.85,0:24:25.80,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,An encounter. Is that the beginning of suffering?
